<dl id="n35018e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35018e">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35018e"> 18(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> brewising the bed</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">BRUISING, or rather BREWISING, THE BED. Bewraying the bed; from Brewes <font color="green">[the fat scum from the pot in which salted beef is boiled]</font>. <small> Captain Francis Grose, <a name="FGCD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FGCD"><cite title="source">A Classical Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue</cite></a> (1785) 00</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
